ciscoMauExtMIB.name: ciscoMauExtMIB

revisions.description: Added cmExtIfMauTrafficTable Added cmExtIfMauTrafficGroup OBJECT-GROUP Deprecated cmExtMIBCompliance2 MODULE-COMPLIANCE Added cmExtMIBCompliance3 MODULE-COMPLIANCE
Initial version of this MIB module.

ciscoMauExtMIB.contactinfo: Cisco Systems Customer Service Postal: 170 W Tasman Drive San Jose, CA 95134 USA Tel: +1 800 553-NETS E-mail: cs-lan-switch-snmp@cisco.com
ciscoMauExtMIB.description: A MIB module for extending the MAU-MIB (RFC 3636) to add objects which provide additional management information about MAU or Jack not available in MAU-MIB.

cmExtJackConfigTable.name: cmExtJackConfigTable
cmExtJackConfigTable.description: This table contains management information about MAUs attached to interfaces with managed jacks. The objects in this table are in addition to the objects in the ifJackTable.

cmExtJackConfigEntry.name: cmExtJackConfigEntry
cmExtJackConfigEntry.description: An entry containing additional management information for a particular jack.

cmExtJackState.name: cmExtJackState
cmExtJackState.description: Indicates the state of a particular jack. Within a particular MAU, setting this to 'active' on a jack which is not the current active jack will deactivate the current active jack. Setting the current active jack to 'active' has no effect. A value of inactive(2) indicates that the jack is currently deactiveated. Setting this to 'inactive' has no effect. Of all the jacks connected to a MAU, at least one must be active at all times.

cmExtIfAutoMdixConfigTable.name: cmExtIfAutoMdixConfigTable
cmExtIfAutoMdixConfigTable.description: This table contains Auto-MDIX configuration information for MAUs attached to interfaces in the device. An entry appears in this table for each active Auto-MDIX capable MAU connected to interfaces in the device.

cmExtIfAutoMdixConfigEntry.name: cmExtIfAutoMdixConfigEntry
cmExtIfAutoMdixConfigEntry.description: An entry containing Auto-MDIX configuration information for a MAU connected to the interface.

cmExtIfAutoMdixEnabled.name: cmExtIfAutoMdixEnabled
cmExtIfAutoMdixEnabled.description: Specifies if Auto-MDIX feature is enabled on the MAU.

cmExtIfMauTrafficTable.name: cmExtIfMauTrafficTable
cmExtIfMauTrafficTable.description: The (conceptual) table that identifies the type of traffic carried by the interfaces associated with the MAUs in the device. This table is sparse dependant on ifMauTable.

cmExtIfMauTrafficEntry.name: cmExtIfMauTrafficEntry
cmExtIfMauTrafficEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in the cmExtIfMauTrafficEntry. Each entry contains the type of traffic carried by the interface associated with the MAU identified by the indices.

cmExtIfMauTrafficType.name: cmExtIfMauTrafficType
cmExtIfMauTrafficType.description: This object is used to identify the type of traffic carried by the MAU. This object can take the following values other(1) - The traffic type is other than anything defined below adminControl(2) - This interface carries administrative and control traffic that is internal to the device user(3) - This interface carries the user data traffic

cmExtMIBCompliance.name: cmExtMIBCompliance
cmExtMIBCompliance.description: The compliance statement for entities which implement the Cisco MAU extension MIB.

cmExtMIBCompliance2.name: cmExtMIBCompliance2
cmExtMIBCompliance2.description: The compliance statement for entities which implement the Cisco MAU extension MIB.

cmExtMIBCompliance3.name: cmExtMIBCompliance3
cmExtMIBCompliance3.description: The compliance statement for entities which implement the Cisco MAU extension MIB.

cmExtJackConfigGroup.name: cmExtJackConfigGroup
cmExtJackConfigGroup.description: A collection of objects providing the configuration information about MAUs attached to interfaces with managed jacks.

cmExtIfAutoMdixConfigGroup.name: cmExtIfAutoMdixConfigGroup
cmExtIfAutoMdixConfigGroup.description: A collection of objects providing the configuration information of Auto-MDIX feature in the device.

cmExtIfMauTrafficGroup.name: cmExtIfMauTrafficGroup
cmExtIfMauTrafficGroup.description: Object that provides the type of traffic carried by MAUs in devices having admin or control traffic internal to the device.
